Package: kanotix-kernelhacking
Architecture: all
Recommends: kanotix-modules, dpatch, dpkg-dev, fakeroot
Replaces: kanotix-modules (<<2.6.13.6)
Description: various tools for kernel hacking
 These tools script common tasks while testing kernels, like creating kbuild 
 symlinks, removal of deprecated kernel images and associated drivers or a 
 custom Makefile for /usr/src/.

Package: kanotix-modules
Architecture: all
Depends: bzip2, kanotix-su, unp, zip, gawk, acx-source, acer-acpi-source, adm8211-source, at76c503a-source, btsco-source, cloop-src, fsam7400-source, gspca-source, ibdriver-source, ipw3945-source, ivtv-source, linux-wlan-ng-source, lirc-modules-source, ndiswrapper-source, qc-usb-source, rt2400-source, rt2500-source, rt2570-source, rt61-source, rfswitch-source, rtl8180-sa2400-source, squashfs-source, unionfs-source, usbvision-source
Recommends: acerhk-source
Suggests: kanotix-kernelhacking
Description: meta package for KANOTIX kernel modules
 Depend on commonly used kernel module sources for easy kernel hacking and
 provide easy scripts to unpack those or remove older kernels.
